  "texts": [
    "Unlike text content, the propagation graph is beyond the control of the spreaders.",
    "Therefore, propagation-based methods exhibit greater resilience against malicious actors.",
    "However, they are less effective in detecting disinformation at an early stage.",
    "As a result, recent research has sought to combine the advantages of both content-based (such as text) and context-based (such as propagation graph) methods to create more effective models for disinformation detection.",
    "Social networks inherently form a rich and interconnected graph structure."
  ],
